<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1736,1904]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">
Species in this genus are mostly parasitoids of whiteflies and armoured scale insects (
<taxonomicName box="[1109,1249,1736,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Diaspididae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Diaspididae</taxonomicName>
), and are of considerable economic importance. The systematics and biology of the genus are treated in detail by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="5" pageNumber="59" refString="Heraty, J. M., Polaszek, A. &amp; Schauff, M. E. (2008) Systematics and Biology of Encarsia. Chapter 4, pp. 71 - 87, in: Gould, J., Hoelmer, K. and Goolsby, J. Classical Biological Control of Bemisia tabaci in the United States. A review of interagency research and implementation. Springer, 343 pp." type="book chapter">
Heraty 
<emphasis box="[1377,1429,1772,1796]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[159,221,1808,1832]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" value="2008.0">2008</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Morphological terminology follows 
<bibRefCitation author="Schmidt" box="[656,976,1808,1832]" pageId="5" pageNumber="59" refString="Schmidt S, Polaszek A. (2007) Encarsia or Encarsiella? - redefining generic limits based on morphological and molecular evidence (Hymenoptera, Aphelinidae). Systematic Entomology, 32, 81 - 94." type="journal article" year="2007">
Schmidt &amp; Polaszek (
<number box="[907,969,1808,1832]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" value="2007.0">2007</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. All specimens studied in this paper are deposited in the following collections: 
<collectionCode box="[593,681,1845,1868]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/p1gh-na36" name="Bombay Natural History Museum" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">BNHM</collectionCode>
: Natural History Museum, London, 
<collectingCountry box="[1092,1136,1845,1868]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">UK</collectingCountry>
; UCR: University of California, Riverside, 
<collectingCountry box="[353,413,1880,1904]" name="United States of America" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">USA</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
